Yay yelp!  We found El Laurel because of you and loved it!  I don't  think you can go wrong with any of empanadas or salads.  As a family of four we ordered whole bunch of things and shared them.  All were delicious.  The patrons and staff are mostly local and seem to hang out regularly.  Not a lot of english but there is an english menu and they met us half way.  Wish I could go there now!
